{"thought": "The issue is about WKT1-based transformation failing while proj4-based transformation succeeds. 

The WKT1 string defines a Sinusoidal projection with a custom spheroid (R=6371007.181). When parsed as WKT1, the forward transform produces NaN. But when the equivalent proj4 string `+proj=sinu +lon_0=0 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +R=6371007.181 +units=m +no_defs +type=crs` is used, it works correctly.

This suggests the WKT1 parser (likely in the wkt-parser dependency or in the parseCode.js) is not correctly extracting the spheroid parameters (specifically R or a/b) from the WKT1 string. Let me explore the parseCode.js and related files to understand how WKT parsing works."}

